If the spell has any targets, you may choose new targets for the copy."'}, {'date': '2022-04-29', 'text': 'If you pay the casualty cost of a spell, the copy will resolve before the original spell.'}, {'date': '2022-04-29', 'text': "The copied spell from Ob Nixilis, the Adversary's triggered ability copies exactly what is printed on Ob Nixilis, except its starting loyalty is equal to the chosen value of X and it isn't legendary. The copy becomes a token as it resolves."}, {'date': '2022-04-29', 'text': 'The copy of the spell is created on the stack, so it\'s not "cast." If you pay the overload cost, the spell won't have any targets."}, {'date': '2024-01-12', 'text': "To determine the total cost of a spell, start with the mana cost or alternative cost you're paying (such as an overload cost), add any cost increases, then apply any cost reductions. rulings: [{'date': '2016-01-22', 'text': 'Mana produced by Cultivator Drone may be used to cast any colorless spell, including most artifact spells, face-down spells, and spells with devoid.'}, {'date': '2016-01-22', 'text': 'Some triggered abilities include a cost as part of their resolution. In fact, you could tap two Cultivator Drones to pay the entire cost.'}]

name: Celestial Colonnade
text:
This land enters tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {U}.
{3}{W}{U}: Until end of turn, this land becomes a 4/4 white and blue Elemental creature with flying and vigilance. It's still a land.
rulings: [{'date': '2010-03-01', 'text': 'A land that becomes a creature may be affected by "summoning sickness." You can\'t attack with it or use any of its {T} abilities (including its mana abilities) unless it began your most recent turn on the battlefield under your control. Note that summoning sickness cares about when that permanent came under your control, not when it became a creature.'}, {'date': '2010-03-01', 'text': "When a land becomes a creature, that doesn't count as having a creature enter. The permanent was already on the battlefield; it only changed its types. Abilities that trigger whenever a creature enters won't trigger."}, {'date': '2018-12-07', 'text': "If Celestial Colonnade can't attack unless you pay a cost that includes a mana payment, you may attack with it and tap it to pay for that cost. It will still attack in this case."}, {'date': '2018-12-07', 'text': "Once Celestial Colonnade has attacked, tapping it for mana won't remove it from combat."}]
full_text:
This land enters tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {U}.
{3}{W}{U}: Until end of turn, this land becomes a 4/4 white and blue Elemental creature with flying and vigilance. It's still a land. Land
